},"mentionCount":1,"sources":[{"kind":"description","sourceRecordId":null,"label":"description","matchedText":"ZAI-10"}]},{"issue":{"id":"9660db7b-34d3-4301-93fc-d91bc4ff8362","identifier":"ZAI-58","title":"fix(dialog): center alignment broken on md+ in Tailwind v4","status":"done","priority":"high","assigneeAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","assigneeUserId":null},"mentionCount":1,"sources":[{"kind":"description","sourceRecordId":null,"label":"description","matchedText":"ZAI-10"}]},{"issue":{"id":"40160a21-ce32-4672-aaf2-542e673a3ab6","identifier":"ZAI-59","title":"Review productivity for ZAI-10","status":"done","priority":"high","assigneeAgentId":"f46ac66f-1fda-464c-8df7-50fe2412e5b8","assigneeUserId":null},"mentionCount":1,"sources":[{"kind":"comment","sourceRecordId":"3d2f744a-ea30-4bbd-99f1-fef6719b9ad8","label":"comment","matchedText":"ZAI-10"}]},{"issue":{"id":"da7701c9-6e95-4065-9ee8-3acff16cec12","identifier":"ZAI-63","title":"ZAI-44-P1: Post-revert Phase 1 sweep — collect ALL hardcoded English + key-parity audit","status":"done","priority":"high","assigneeAgentId":"a6ec4085-a4e5-489c-bd10-7c46f8b62e07","assigneeUserId":null},"mentionCount":1,"sources":[{"kind":"description","sourceRecordId":null,"label":"description","matchedText":"ZAI-10"}]},{"issue":{"id":"dd98ad18-afea-4bd0-b65e-b70f9cccaaa4","identifier":"ZAI-64","title":"ZAI-44-GC-A: i18n CompanyEnvironments.tsx — wire 30+ strings (CRITICAL board-flagged page)","status":"done","priority":"critical","assigneeAgentId":"2c35ae09-781d-4a7c-880b-8abd833fd682","assigneeUserId":null},"mentionCount":1,"sources":[{"kind":"description","sourceRecordId":null,"label":"description","matchedText":"ZAI-10"}]},{"issue":{"id":"3953d305-4584-4776-9a72-c2d2a53aaf86","identifier":"ZAI-67","title":"Co-Authored-By: Paperclip <noreply@paperclip.ing>","status":"done","priority":"medium","assigneeAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","assigneeUserId":null},"mentionCount":1,"sources":[{"kind":"comment","sourceRecordId":"fd0ad646-1ebb-4e07-b945-af1aaadbddff","label":"comment","matchedText":"ZAI-10"}]}]},"referencedIssueIdentifiers":["ZAI-44","ZAI-43","ZAI-45","ZAI-12","ZAI-58","ZAI-22","ZAI-23","ZAI-42","ZAI-7","ZAI-18","ZAI-59","ZAI-13","ZAI-14","ZAI-15","ZAI-16","ZAI-17","ZAI-19","ZAI-20","ZAI-21","ZAI-46","ZAI-57"],"planDocument":{"id":"7f74178b-9e80-465f-ab83-94ba637485fc","companyId":"13e61789-5895-451b-95a8-a7457a310c9e","issueId":"e35807e7-7c2a-4ce2-a567-33c86b1cba7c","key":"plan","title":"Plan","format":"markdown","body":"# Plan — Complete Localization Project (ZAI-10)\n\n## Current state\n\n- 8 locales live: en, de, el, es, pt, ru, uk, zh\n- 15 namespace files per locale (common, agents, issues, company, dashboard, costs, activity, inbox, routines, goals, approvals, settings, adapters, org, onboarding)\n- Reference docs in `ui/src/locales/~temp/`:\n  - `PROJECT_DESIGN.md` — URL → component → locale file map\n  - `UNTRANSLATED_ENGLISH_TEXT_MAP.md` — known gaps as of 2025-04-25 (Russian audit)\n- Uncommitted in-flight work on this branch:\n  - `ui/src/components/Sidebar.tsx` (nav — highest-impact gap)\n  - `server/src/routes/org-chart-svg.ts` (org chart text)\n  - `ui/src/adapters/openclaw-gateway/config-fields.tsx`\n  - `ui/src/lib/user-display.ts` (untracked)\n- Prior productivity-review incident on ZAI-7 (high churn). Scope must be bounded.\n\n## Definition of done\n\nFor every URL in `PROJECT_DESIGN.md`, across all 8 locales:\n1. No hardcoded English visible to a non-English user (ignoring user-generated content and code samples)\n2. No missing-key console warnings for the active locale\n3. Locale switcher works on every listed page\n4. Russian gaps in `UNTRANSLATED_ENGLISH_TEXT_MAP.md` resolved or explicitly deferred with reason\n5. Placeholder strings (e.g. \"Ы\", \"ыва\") removed\n6. In-flight uncommitted work either landed or rolled back with a reason\n\n## Execution plan\n\nOwner: **CTO**. Route execution to the Localization Agent (translation) and Browser Tester Agent (verification).\n\nBreak into bounded child issues — do NOT run as a single open-ended task (ZAI-7 churned at 10 runs/1h on open scope). Suggested decomposition:\n\n1. **Land in-flight work or revert** — single child issue. Decide per-file: ship if complete, revert if speculative. Includes user-display.ts.\n2. **Sidebar + global chrome (HIGH)** — one child issue. Nav menu, command palette, account menu, top bar, \"Skip to main content\". All 8 locales.\n3. **Per-page sweep** — one child issue per page-group (Dashboard, Issues+Detail, Agents+Detail, Projects, Costs, Activity, Inbox, Goals, Routines, Approvals, Org, Skills, Settings, Adapters, Onboarding). Each page-group fixes hardcoded strings and adds keys to all 8 locales. Run in parallel where possible.\n4. **Server-side response messages** — one child issue. Error/validation strings on `server/src/routes/*` honor `Accept-Language`.\n5. **QA verification matrix** — one child issue per locale assigned to Browser Tester. Walks every URL in `PROJECT_DESIGN.md` with that locale active, records remaining gaps.\n\nEach child issue must:\n- Name the exact file(s) and locale namespace(s) in scope\n- Cap acceptance at \"no untranslated English on listed routes\" — not \"translate everything ever\"\n- Have a single owner and a clear next-action\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- New locale languages\n- Translating user-generated content (issue titles, comments, agent names)\n- Translating embedded markdown/code documentation that lives in `.md` source files (handle separately if requested)\n- RTL layout (no RTL locales in scope)\n\n## Risks / watchouts\n\n- Localization Agent has heartbeat disabled (`heartbeat.enabled: false`). CTO must wake explicitly via assignment, not rely on timer.\n- Browser Tester also heartbeat-disabled. Same handling.\n- Server-side i18n may not exist yet — if so, scope (4) becomes \"design + implement\", not \"translate\". CTO to assess and split if needed.\n","latestRevisionId":"0d5825e1-c012-477c-b594-92e2fdfcebbd","latestRevisionNumber":1,"createdByAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","createdByUserId":null,"updatedByAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","updatedByUserId":null,"createdAt":"2026-05-05T05:52:48.406Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-05T05:52:48.406Z"},"documentSummaries":[{"id":"7f74178b-9e80-465f-ab83-94ba637485fc","companyId":"13e61789-5895-451b-95a8-a7457a310c9e","issueId":"e35807e7-7c2a-4ce2-a567-33c86b1cba7c","key":"plan","title":"Plan","format":"markdown","latestRevisionId":"0d5825e1-c012-477c-b594-92e2fdfcebbd","latestRevisionNumber":1,"createdByAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","createdByUserId":null,"updatedByAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","updatedByUserId":null,"createdAt":"2026-05-05T05:52:48.406Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-05T05:52:48.406Z"}],"legacyPlanDocument":null,"project":{"id":"90d1b267-8b11-4b20-abed-2422cd4089fb","companyId":"13e61789-5895-451b-95a8-a7457a310c9e","goalId":null,"name":"Localization","description":"**Project Goal**\n\nReplace hardcoded English text in UI with localization variables (react-i18next / i18next), while simultaneously ensuring support for two languages: English (en) and Russian (ru). A language switcher dropdown menu is added to the UI, designed according to the project design. The process is executed iteratively by a team of agents until all text elements are fully covered.\n\n**Directory Structure**\n\n```\nC:\\Users\\vibecoder_blogger\\PycharmProjects\\paperclip_fork_Enterprise\\ui\\src\\locales\\\n├── en\\                         # Translation files — English\n├── ru\\                         # Translation files — Russian\n└── ~temp\\\n    ├── PROJECT_DESIGN.md\n    └── HARDCODED_ENGLISH_ELEMENTS_MAP.md\n\n```\n\n**Localization Library**\n\nreact-i18next / i18next — configuration and existing translations are located in: `C:\\Users\\vibecoder_blogger\\PycharmProjects\\paperclip_fork_Enterprise\\ui\\src\\locales`\n\n**Agent Roles**\n\n**Developer** — localization developer: replaces hardcode with `t('key')`, maintains `en\\` and `ru\\` files, implements dropdown menu.\n\n**QA** — browser tester: checks server availability at [`http://127.0.0.1:3105/`](http://127.0.0.1:3105/), searches for unreplaced English strings when Russian language is active, updates MAP file.\n\n**Orchestrator** — monitors the last update date of MAP file; if file is updated — starts new Developer → QA cycle.\n\n**Statuses in MAP File**\n\n| Status         | Set By        | Meaning                                          |\n| -------------- | ------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |\n| TODO           | Browser agent | Found English text, needs localization           |\n| DONE           | Developer     | Localization completed, awaiting QA verification |\n| TODO + comment | QA            | Checked, found problem, returned to Developer    |\n| QA\\_OK         | QA            | Checked, everything works correctly              |\n\n**Working Cycle (Loop)**\n\n```\nBrowser agent → TODO\n      ↓\nDeveloper → DONE\n      ↓\nQA checks DONE\n      ↓\n  [not OK] → TODO + comment → Developer → DONE → QA...\n  [OK]    → QA_OK\n\n```\n\n**Plan**\n\n**Step 1 — Browser agent: audit of visible English elements**\n\n* Opens [http://127.0.0.1:3105/](http://127.0.0.1:3105/), switches to Russian language.\n* Goes through all available screens.\n* For each found English text, records in MAP file:\n  * full element text\n  * HTML element\n  * CSS selector\n  * status TODO\n\n**Step 2 — Developer: hardcode replacement**\n\n* Takes records with TODO status from MAP file.\n* By text, HTML element and CSS selector finds location in codebase.\n* Replaces with t('key'), adds translations to en\\ and ru.\n* Sets status DONE.\n\n**Step 3 — QA: DONE verification**\n\n* Receives signal about appearance of records with DONE status in MAP file.\n* First basic check: [http://127.0.0.1:3105/](http://127.0.0.1:3105/) responds and not black screen. If black screen — cycle stops, Developer fixes.\n* Switches to Russian language, checks specific elements from DONE records.\n* If problem — changes status back to TODO with comment on what exactly is wrong.\n* If everything is correct — sets QA\\_OK.\n\n**Step 4 — Iteration**\n\n* Browser agent again goes through all screens searching for remaining English strings.\n* New strings → TODO, cycle repeats.\n* Orchestrator starts new cycle with each appearance of TODO in MAP file.\n\n**Final Verification (when all records are QA\\_OK)**\n\n* QA goes through all records with QA\\_OK status — full regression run.\n* Checks that previously completed localization hasn't broken during subsequent changes.\n* If something broke — record returns to TODO with comment, cycle resumes.\n* If everything is fine — project is considered completed.\n\n**Completion Criterion**\n\nAll records in MAP file have QA\\_OK status, final regression run is passed, server [http://127.0.0.1:3105/](http://127.0.0.1:3105/) loads stably.","status":"planned","leadAgentId":null,"targetDate":null,"color":"#14b8a6","env":null,"pauseReason":null,"pausedAt":null,"executionWorkspacePolicy":null,"archivedAt":null,"createdAt":"2026-05-04T07:09:48.516Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-06T19:29:42.813Z","urlKey":"localization","goalIds":[],"goals":[],"codebase":{"workspaceId":"047a7078-fce3-46a4-aa5e-d66abc0a3f51","repoUrl":"https://github.com/AngelCard-CC-Non-Cancellation-Guarantee/paperclip_fork_Enterprise.git","repoRef":null,"defaultRef":null,"repoName":"paperclip_fork_Enterprise","localFolder":"C:\\Users\\vibecoder_blogger\\PycharmProjects\\paperclip_fork_Enterprise","managedFolder":"C:\\Users\\vibecoder_blogger\\.paperclip\\instances\\default\\projects\\13e61789-5895-451b-95a8-a7457a310c9e\\90d1b267-8b11-4b20-abed-2422cd4089fb\\paperclip_fork_Enterprise","effectiveLocalFolder":"C:\\Users\\vibecoder_blogger\\PycharmProjects\\paperclip_fork_Enterprise","origin":"local_folder"},"workspaces":[{"id":"047a7078-fce3-46a4